Definition.WordDefinition: Indecipherable \In`de*ci"pher*a*ble\, a. Not decipherable; incapable of being deciphered, explained, or solved. -- {In`de*ci"pher*a*bly}, adv. [1913 Webster]
indecipherable adj 1: not easily deciphered; "indecipherable handwriting" [syn: {unclear}, {undecipherable}, {unreadable}] 2: impossible to determine the meaning of; "an indecipherable message"
